Privacy Policy

Effective Date:18.07.2024

Introduction

Produ values your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our iOS application (the "Produ").

1. Information We Do Not Collect

We want to assure you that when you use our App, we do not collect, store, or process any personal data or information. This includes, but is not limited to, the following types of data:

Personal Identification Information (e.g., name, address, email address, phone number)
Device Information (e.g., IP address, device ID, operating system, browser type)
Usage Data (e.g., app interactions, usage patterns)
Location Information
Cookies and Tracking Technologies
2. Third-Party Services

Since we do not collect any data, we also do not share any data with third-party services. Our App does not integrate with third-party analytics providers, advertisers, or any other services that may collect your data.

3. Data Security

Although we do not collect any data, we are committed to ensuring that our App is secure and free from vulnerabilities. We employ standard security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction of the App.

4. Children's Privacy

Our App does not target or knowingly collect any information from children under the age of 13. Since we do not collect any data, we fully comply with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make any changes, we will notify you by updating the date at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about our data handling practices.

6. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:

Email: erturulkucukkaya@outlook.com 


7. Consent

By using our App, you consent to this Privacy Policy.

8. Disclaimer

Please note that while our App does not collect or store any data, the platform providers (such as Apple) may collect and process your data according to their privacy policies. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of such providers for more information.
